# Build output
*.exe
# ...except the shipped engine: testers get it via Update SangalaStudio.cmd, which
# fetches this committed binary. Rebuild it (Build SangalaStudio.cmd) and commit it
# whenever the engine (.cs) changes, or testers get a stale engine.
!SangalaStudio.exe

# Temp / diagnostic files
_*.png
_*.svg

# Parity-test run artifacts (dev/parity)
dev/parity/_*

# Local snapshot scheme (superseded by git history)
versions/

# Binary design docs — live in Dropbox, not the repo
Houses/*.docx

# Superseded manual versions: the current one is in the repo, its history is in git.
# (Keeping 129 MB of past .docx revisions would bloat every clone a school makes.)
.Archive/

# Source photos and screenshots for the documents — same reason: 20 MB of PNG/JPG
# (one 16 MB silhouette source alone) would sit in every clone forever. Keep the
# originals in Dropbox; the documents carry their own embedded copies.
Images/

# Printable artifacts (sample inserts, doc exports for eyeballing) — output, not
# source. The design that produced them is the .svg or .docx that IS tracked.
*.pdf

# OS / Dropbox / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.dropbox
.dropbox.attr
~$*

# Claude Code: commit shared settings.json, ignore machine-specific local settings
.claude/settings.local.json

# local sync bookkeeping for Sync with Dropbox.cmd
tools/.publish-state.json
tools/sync-log.txt
SYNC CONFLICT.txt
